main event: A couple observed a cigar-shaped white object moving in the sky over Rochester, New York, on October 4, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes., The object appeared to move from easterly to northerly directions., The object was visible to the naked eye and seemed larger than a star., The object's motion could have been mistaken for that of an aircraft., The object was later concluded to be the ECHO II satellite.
witness description: a couple and their daughter; the husband was an engineer with Xerox and a former Air Force Reserve Captain
